default12
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLack ofdefault idefaultmpact:default defaultPHSO’s own figures show 
defaultthat, in 2012-2013, they received over 24,000 complaints about the NHS or Government departments. Of these, they completed 384 investigations which 
defaultwas
default less than 2% of all complaints received. Therefore, the learning from complaints is limited to a relatively small number of complaints and the impact is minimised.  
defaultAs noted earlier, this poor level of impact is a key factor in clients ’decisions not to take their case to PHSO. 
default&#xa0;
defaultPHSO and Advocacydefault&#xa0;default13
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOur experience shows that advice and advocacy services provide an important and independent link between the service provider and the client. We provide our clients with the confidence and tools to voice their concerns and to ensure improvements are made as a result. 
default&#xa0;
default14
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAdvocacy and advice can support a complainant, help PHSO with its communication and ensure that the process is balanced and fair. 
defaultWe believe PHSO could benefit from creating stronger links with advice and advocacy providers 
defaultwho are trained in this field. 
defaultA survey conducted by PHSO in 2
default011 and shared with ICAS providers showed that of all the advice and advocacy organisations they surveyed
default,
default knowledge of PHSO and a good understanding of the service it provided was very significantly higher
default in the NHS complaints advocacy service
default than in other advice and advocacy agencies. 
defaultFurthermore, the take up rate for health cases supported by 
defaultspecialist NHS complaints advocates
default is three times that of the general PHSO take up rate. 
default&#xa0;
default15
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCurrently PHSO provides a link on its website to an organisation calling itself ‘NHS Advocacy Services’. Not only is this link b
defaulturied in the site and fails to
default appear when you search the site using the term ‘advocacy’, it also links to only one 
defaultadvocacy provider
default cover
defaults only a limited part 
defaultof England. This discriminates against vulnerable clients in all other geographical areas and causes 
defaultconfusion for the complainant as there is no signposting to providers in their area. 
default We have also not been able to meet with the Ombudsman in over a year to discuss how we can work together for the benefit of complainant
default.
